der.com%2Fmother-moved-daughter-miles-away-chicago-pain-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ein%20Chicago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we've%20been%20around%20since%202011.%20It%20started%20as%20a%20bicycle%20manufacturing%20company%2C%20and%20I%20paired%20that%20with%20a%20caf%C3%A9.%20I%20did%20that%20for%20a%20few%20years%20as%20I%20pursued%20my%20interests%20throughout%20the%20hospitality%20industry.%20We%20now%20have%20five%20different%20brands%3A%20Froth%2C%20Heritage%20Outpost%2C%20Heritage%20Bikes%20%26amp%3B%20Coffee%2C%20Larry's%2C%20and%20Bunker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20the%20customers.%20I%20love%20solving%20the%20problems%20that%20arise.%20I%20love%20experimenting%20with%20food.%20I%20love%20coming%20up%20with%20new%20drinks.%20I%20love%20my%20employees%2C%20and%20the%20interactions%20I%20have%20with%20everybody%20I%20get%20to%20work%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20have%20tariffs%20or%20other%20factors%20affected%20your%20business%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20mhoff%40businessinsider.com.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20teenager%20is%20now%20working%20at%20the%20shop%20as%20a%20dishwasher.%20That's%20so%20fun%20to%20see.%20We%20started%20this%20company%20when%20he%20was%20several%20months%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20always%20been%20about%20the%20people%2C%20it's%20always%20been%20about%20the%20hospitality%2C%20and%20that%20keeps%20me%20going.%20I%20love%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fin-2020-big-businesses-got-bigger-small-businesses-died-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECOVID%20was%20one%20of%20the%20hardest%3C%2Fa%3E%20points%20in%20my%20life%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eoperating%20a%20business.%20Everything%20was%20uncertain%2C%20and%20everything%20was%20shut%20down.%20We%20paused%2C%20we%20took%20a%20break%2C%20and%20figured%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20everything's%20uncertain%2C%20but%20no%20one's%20giving%20it%20the%20attention%20it%20needs.%20The%20current%20moment%20with%20inflation%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-trump-tariff-uncertainty-affecting-businesses-spending-prices-hiring-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epolicy%20uncertainty%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20starting%20to%20rival%20running%20a%20business%20during%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e5169d8-d850-41fc-ae1a-22cfc22eef20%5C%22%3EIt%20feels%20like%20tariffs%20are%20hitting%20almost%20every%20aspect%20of%20the%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20bicycle%20parts%2C%20anything%20coming%20from%20overseas%2C%20that's%20getting%20hit%2C%20whether%20it's%20tariffs%20or%20lack%20of%20inventory%20at%20this%20point%2C%20because%20the%20wholesalers%20don't%20have%20it%20either.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-coffee-is-more-expensive-roasters-cafe-owners-prices-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECoffee%20bean%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20obviously%20gone%20up.%20Tariffs%20on%20South%20America%2C%20Brazil%20in%20particular%2C%20have%20carried%20that%20weight%20of%20the%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20things%20like%20cups%2C%20paper%20goods%2C%20anything%20that%20we%20rely%20on%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%2C%20nothing's%20manufactured%20in%20the%20States.%20It's%20a%20global%20economy%2C%20so%20everything%20gets%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20issue%20is%20not%20knowing%20what%20is%20going%20on.%20You%20can't%20operate%20a%20business%20with%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20day%20is%20a%20win%20or%20a%20loss%2C%20and%20you%20can't%20really%20run%20a%20business%20that%20way.%20This%20uncertainty%20creates%20this%20temperature%20where%20I'm%20going%20to%20hold%20off%20on%20any%20major%20decisions%20because%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20that's%20going%20to%20affect%20my%20bottom%20line%20tomorrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20uncertainty%20stems%20from%20a%20few%20factors.%20It's%20tariffs%2C%20it's%20political%2C%20it's%20immigration%2C%20it's%20labor.%20We're%20going%20into%20the%20slow%20season.%20That's%20going%20to%20be%20uncertain.%20I'm%20frozen%20for%20at%20least%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20like%20we're%20operating%20in%20a%20hurricane%20with%20all%20these%20things%20flying%20in%20our%20faces%2C%20and%20we're%20just%20trying%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20kitchen's%20open%20and%20the%20coffee's%20warm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226cb6e5b1-7770-47b4-89bd-1593253de8e7%5C%22%3EWe%20just%20raised%20prices%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20although%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-trade-tariffs-consumers-import-costs-inflation-goldman-sachs-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETariffs%20are%20a%20key%20reason%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20we're%20also%20raising%20prices%20due%20to%20across-the-board%20cost%20increases%3A%20labor%2C%20insurance%2C%20coffee%2C%20paper%20goods.%20Everything%20is%20up.%20Tariffs%20were%20the%20tipping%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20raising%20prices%20in%20stages%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoffee-shops-raise-prices-trump-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estarting%20with%20coffee%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Next%2C%20we're%20looking%20at%20pastries%2C%20packaged%20drinks%2C%20and%20eventually%20our%20food%20menu.%20We're%20reviewing%20item%20by%20item%20over%20the%20next%20two%20months%20and%20adjusting%20where%20the%20margin%20hit%20is%20greatest.%20We're%20not%20taking%20a%20blanket%20approach%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20strategic%20and%20staged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Froth%2C%20we%20raised%20the%20price%20of%20a%20cappuccino%20from%20%244.50%20to%20%244.75.%20A%2012-ounce%20drip%20coffee%20went%20from%20%243.00%20to%20%243.15.%20A%20cold%20brew%20went%20from%20%244.75%20to%20%245.00.%20At%20Heritage%20Bikes%20%26amp%3B%20Coffee%2C%20a%20cortado%20went%20from%20%244.25%20to%20%244.50.%20Most%20changes%20were%20in%20that%205%25%20range%2C%20rounded%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20want%20to%20bombard%20everybody%2C%20but%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20done.%20Right%20now%2C%20we%20are%20just%20increasing%20prices%20on%20coffee%20drinks%2C%20where%20we%20lost%20a%20ton%20of%20margin%2C%20and%20I%20needed%20to%20recoup%20some%20of%20that.%20So%20that's%20where%20the%20first%20step%20was.%20We'll%20continue%20to%20do%20that%20throughout%20the%20next%20few%20months%20and%20slowly%20but%20surely%20raise%20prices%20where%20it%20makes%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaising%20prices%20is%20really%20hard%20for%20me.%20It's%20been%20years%20since%20I've%20done%20that%20for%20coffee.%20It%20needed%20to%20be%20done%20because%20I%20see%20that%20we're%20making%20more%20revenue%2C%20but%20we%20have%20less%20margin%20for%20any%20profit%20to%20pay%20our%20folks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurants-pass-higher-food-costs-diners-inflation-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eraising%20prices%20on%20my%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20come%20in%20and%20spend%20their%20money%20on%20a%20coffee%2C%20bike%2C%20service%2C%20beer%2C%20or%20food.%20Growing%20up%2C%20we%20didn't%20really%20go%20out%20of%20our%20way%20to%20go%20out%20to%20coffee%20or%20go%20to%20the%20local%20restaurants.%20So%20I%20know%20how%20special%20that%20can%20be.%20I've%20always%20wanted%20that%20to%20be%20within%20striking%20distance%20of%20most%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20debated%20announcing%20the%20increase%20widely%20by%20email%2C%20but%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20explain%20it%20directly%20when%20asked%2C%20which%20felt%20more%20aligned%20with%20how%20we%20do%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReactions%20have%20been%20surprisingly%20quiet.%20Most%20people%20haven't%20noticed%20or%20haven't%20said%20anything.%20A%20few%20regulars%20asked%20about%20the%20change%2C%20and%20when%20we%20explained%20it%20was%20tariff%20and%20cost-related%2C%20they%20nodded%20and%20moved%20on.%20I%20think%20people%20generally%20understand%20that%20everything%20is%20getting%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20look%20at%20what%20our%20margins%20are%20and%20how%20thin%20they've%20become%20in%20order%20to%20operate%2C%20I've%20had%20to%20raise%20those%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2810ae4-e389-47d5-8714-918abcd49b3b%5C%22%3EWe've%20had%20to%20make%20some%20drawbacks%20on%20staff%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20cut%20staff%20in%20September%20due%20to%20tariffs%2C%20but%20also%20to%20streamline%20operations%20in%20response%20to%20thinning%20margins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20key%20points%20where%20we%20thought%20we%20could%20run%20more%20efficiently.%20Our%20margin%20for%20labor%2C%20it%20should%20be%20a%20certain%20point%2C%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20your%20income.%20We%20couldn't%20meet%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20operational%20changes%20focused%20on%20efficiency%20%E2%80%94%20eliminating%20overlapping%20shifts%2C%20reducing%20prep%20cook%20hours%2C%20and%20cutting%20a%20few%20key%20middle-management%20roles%20like%20kitchen%20manager%2C%20events%2C%20and%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20love%20to%20be%20able%20to%20have%20someone%20on%20social%20media%20and%20marketing.%20It%20would%20help%20business%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20would%20help%20it%20enough%20to%20make%20up%20for%20their%20salary%20at%20this%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20implemented%20a%20hiring%20freeze%20in%20late%20September%20due%20to%20tariffs%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-purchases-financial-risks-economic-uncertainty-real-estate-careers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20uncertainty%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20broadly.%20We're%20being%20extremely%20selective%20so%20while%20there%20may%20be%20a%20few%20specific%20roles%20open%20(like%20event-based%20or%20part-time)%2C%20we've%20halted%20active%20recruiting%20across%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0aceaaf-8586-471a-a9ad-c61ce9803064%5C%22%3EDespite%20having%20one%20of%20our%20best%20years%20in%20terms%20of%20revenue%2C%20our%20net%20profit%20is%20smaller%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20coming%20in.%20People%20are%20buying.%20Even%20with%20that%2C%20even%20with%20great%20revenue%20coming%20in%2C%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoffee-prices-futures-soaring-climate-change-drought-bitter-beans-flavor-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecoffee%20prices%20went%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20paper%20goods%20went%20up%2C%20because%20labor%20went%20up%2C%20because%20insurance%20went%20up%2C%20every%20line%20item%20in%20our%20expense%20sheet%20has%20gone%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20operating%20at%20thin%20margins%20as%20it%20is%2C%20those%20matter%20hugely.%20So%20if%20you're%20talking%20about%20every%20expense%20that's%20gone%20up%20throughout%20your%20QuickBooks%20account%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20much%20revenue%20comes%20in%2C%20unless%20you%20have%20an%20incredible%20year%2C%20you%20can't%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20expenses%20unless%20you%20raise%20your%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20group%2C%20as%20a%20management%2C%20we%20talk%20about%20finances%20weekly.%20We're%20planning%20for%20those%20slower%20months%2C%20making%20sure%20that%20we%20are%20realistic%20about%20the%20hours%20we%20can%20provide%20for%20our%20staff.%20We're%20realistic%20about%20what%20we%20can%20offer%2C%20what%20we%20can%20buy%2C%20just%20trying%20to%20run%20a%20skeleton%20operation%20until%20we%20understand%20where%20the%20other%20side%20of%20this%20is.%20I'm%20not%20necessarily%20going%20to%20have%20to%20take%20out%20loans%20or%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20try%20to%20operate%20within%20our%20revenues.%20As%20long%20as%20we%20can%20do%20that%20week%20to%20week%2C%20we%20keep%20track%20of%20what's%20going%20on%20week%20to%20week%2C%20we%20make%20sure%20we're%20running%20cost%20of%20goods%2C%20labor%20within%20line%20of%20a%20certain%20formula%2C%20we'll%20be%20OK.%20B