ai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExcel%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Word%20that%20can%20generate%20documents%20and%20spreadsheets.%20It%20lets%20people%20without%20deep%20knowledge%20of%20spreadsheets%20%26quot%3Bspeak%20Excel%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bvibe%20write%26quot%3B%20in%20Word%20by%20generating%2C%20refining%2C%20and%20asking%20the%20author%20questions%20as%20they%20go.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-new-vibes-feed-ai-slop-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMea's%20AI%20app%20now%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bvibes%26quot%3B%20feed%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20AI-generated%20video%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsora-video-app-openai-pros-cons-explained-why-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESora's%3C%2Fa%3E%20AI%20video%20platform%20is%20giving%20rise%20to%20what%20some%20are%20calling%20%26quot%3Bvibe%20creators%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20no%20longer%20traditional%20influencer%20content%2C%20but%20a%20new%20type%20of%20influence%20created%20by%20synthetic%20AI%20imagery%20and%20a%20few%20clicks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWelcome%20to%20the%20vibening%2C%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20white-collar%20work%20is%20being%20portrayed%20as%20just%20vibes.%20The%20term%20is%20shorthand%20for%20using%20generative%20AI%20to%20do%20the%20tedious%20and%20strenuous%20parts%20of%20a%20project%2C%20but%20it%20also%20conveys%20the%20idea%20that%20work%20is%20free-flowing%2C%20improvised%2C%20and%20easy.%20Vibing%20is%20a%20sort%20of%20Gen%20Z%20take%20on%20%3Cem%3Ehygge%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20slang%20that%20was%20once%20reserved%20for%20chilling%20with%20friends%20or%20describing%20a%20date%20gone%20right%20and%20has%20now%20seeped%20its%20way%20into%20corporate%20speak.%20Managers%20hold%20regular%20%26quot%3Bvibe%20checks%26quot%3B%20with%20their%20direct%20reports.%20Some%20companies%20have%20played%20with%20a%20%26quot%3BChief%20Vibe%20Officer%26quot%3B%20title.%20Smirnoff%20announced%20Troye%20Sivan%20into%20the%20role%20as%20part%20of%20a%20promotional%20partnership%20last%20year%2C%20and%20software%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlassian.com%2Fblog%2Fteamwork%2Fchief-vibes-officer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAtlassian%3C%2Fa%3E%20nominated%20a%20rotating%20CVO%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20grow%20bonds%20between%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20vibe%20working%20is%20still%20work.%20Working%20with%20AI%2C%20and%20doing%20it%20well%2C%20takes%20experimentation%20and%20expertise.%20The%20rise%20of%20talk%20of%20vibing%20at%20work%20may%20obfuscate%20the%20value%20of%20mastering%20concepts%20and%20skills%2C%20or%20the%20term%20could%20be%20the%20bat%20signal%20of%20a%20company%20seeking%20energetic%20workers%20who%20want%20to%20experiment.%20If%20it's%20an%20attempt%20by%20companies%20and%20executives%20to%20convey%20they're%20open%20to%20AI%20and%20hip%2C%20the%20imprecise%20language%20and%20experimentation%20can%20be%20a%20recipe%20for%20confusion.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20might%20have%20a%20different%20interpretation%20of%20what%20the%20vibe%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ben%20Armstrong%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20MIT's%20Industrial%20Performance%20Center.%20%26quot%3BOne%20person's%20good%20vibe%20could%20be%20the%20other%20person's%20bad%20vibe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20happens%20when%20the%20vibes%20are%20bad%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20surprising%20to%20see%20the%20idea%20of%20vibe%20work%20gaining%20traction%2C%20as%20Gen%20Z%20sees%20the%20parameters%20of%20work%20with%20blurrier%20lines.%20From%20the%20lazy%20girl%20job%20to%20quiet%20quitting%2C%20there's%20less%20formality%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20and%20young%20people%20are%20less%20interested%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-loyalty-corporate-america-dysfunction-employers-employees-att-jobs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkplace%20loyalty%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustles-freelance-economy-ai-technology-cheap-income-pay-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20dependent%20on%20the%209%20to%205%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Workers%20feel%20disengaged%20with%20corporate%20culture%2C%20so%20a%20rebrand%20to%20the%20gentler%20idea%20of%20vibing%20could%20be%20an%20attempt%20to%20attract%20workers%20to%20a%20less%20rigid%20workplace.%20%26quot%3BI%20imagine%20to%20this%20particular%20demographic%20of%20people%2C%20that's%20very%20appealing%3A%20work%20being%20about%20vibing%20more%20than%20it's%20about%20analyzing%20or%20synthesizing%20or%20reporting%2C%20which%20I%20don't%20think%20sounds%20particularly%20artistic%20or%20creative%20or%20collaborative%20or%20beautiful%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Emily%20DeJeu%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20University's%20Tepper%20School%20of%20Business.%20But%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bhides%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20it%20is%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20DeJeu%20says.%20If%20executives%20rebrand%20work%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bvibe%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20may%20undercut%20the%20necessary%20expertise%20needed%20to%20do%20a%20job.%20That%20could%20become%20exploitative%20if%20bosses%20rely%20on%20workers'%20mastery%20of%20skills%20but%20simultaneously%20write%20off%20the%20value%20of%20work%20performed%20alongside%20AI.%20DeJeu%20likens%20vibe%20coding%20or%20working%20to%20jazz.%20A%20performance%20might%20be%20largely%20improvised%20and%20seem%20effortless%20to%20the%20listener%2C%20but%20that%20vibing%20on%20the%20spot%20only%20works%20because%20musicians%20have%20spent%20years%20mastering%20theory%20before%20taking%20steps%20to%20mess%20it%20all%20up.%20%26quot%3BLabor%20is%20labor%2C%20and%20the%20labor%20to%20build%20expertise%20is%20laborious%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20The%20idea%20that%20you%20can%20vibe%20and%20%26quot%3Byou%20don't%20have%20to%20spend%20all%20that%20time%20and%20it's%20not%20hard%2C%20is%20kind%20of%20laughable%20in%20my%20opinion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVibing%20hasn't%20been%20the%20silver%20bullet%20for%20coding%20some%20expected.%20There's%20been%20a%20frenzy%20for%20AI-generated%20code%2C%20and%20OpenAI's%20Andrej%20Karpathy%20coined%20the%20process%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-limits-use-cases-software-companies-airtable-redis-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evibe%20coding%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20concept%20has%20thrown%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-ladder-software-engineers-collapsing-ai-google-meta-coding-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoftware%20developer%3C%2Fa%3E%20role%20into%20a%20new%20era%20%E2%80%94%20the%20nature%20of%20work%20done%20by%20many%20has%20shifted%20from%20writing%20code%20to%20an%20emphasis%20on%20reviewing%20AI-generated%20code%20for%20bugs%2C%20and%20coders%20aren't%20necessarily%20saving%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20has%20caught%20on%2C%20and%20employers%20are%20hungry%20for%20employees%20who%20know%20how%20to%20use%20AI.%20They're%20eager%20to%20deploy%20cost%20savings%20and%20find%20the%20productivity%20gains%20touted%20by%20AI%20evangelists.%20Even%20though%20most%20companies%20aren't%20training%20people%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20they%20want%20workers%20who%20get%20it%3A%2071%25%20percent%20of%20business%20leaders%20say%20they%20would%20take%20a%20job%20seeker%20with%20less%20experience%20who%20has%20AI%20skills%20over%20a%20more%20experienced%20worker%20who%20doesn't%20know%20how%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20according%20to%20a%202024%20report%20from%20Microsoft.%20Two-thirds%20say%20they%20wouldn't%20hire%20someone%20without%20AI%20knowledge.%20But%20less%20than%20a%20third%20of%20workers%20have%20received%20company%20training%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20according%20to%20a%20survey%20of%20workers%20conducted%20by%20Jobs%20for%20the%20Future%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20focused%20on%20transforming%20the%20workforce.%20There's%20a%20big%20gap%20in%20what%20companies%20want%20in%20terms%20of%20AI%20and%20how%20they're%20able%20to%20convey%20that%20and%20train%20their%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20cope%2C%20workers%20have%20jumped%20on%20AI%20themselves.%20Learning%20about%20the%20tech%20is%20often%20happening%20bottom-up%20from%20workers%20rather%20than%20top-down%20through%20training.%20Workers%20are%20experimenting%20in%20ways%20that%20aren't%20always%20tracked%2C%20so%20the%20best%20practices%20are%20being%20built%20just%20as%20the%20tech's%20limitations%20are%20discovered.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20a%20vibe%20is%20so%20open%20to%20interpretation%2C%20it's%20so%20hard%20to%20measure%20what%20the%20outcome%20of%20these%20different%20tasks%20might%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Armstrong%20says.%20We're%20in%20a%20time%20similar%20to%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20internet%2C%20he%20says%2C%20when%20people%20were%20experimenting%20and%20developing%20different%20types%20of%20web%20interfaces.%20With%20AI%20tools%2C%20people%20are%20%26quot%3Bfiguring%20out%20when%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20effective%2C%20when%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20reliable.%26quot%3B%20All%20of%20that%20vibing%20can%20create%20vastly%20different%20processes%20with%20varying%20degrees%20of%20success%20that%20also%20prove%20hard%20to%20replicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20vibework%20too%20hard%2C%20when%20they%20use%20generative%20AI%20without%20thought%2C%20they%20can%20produce%20mounds%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkslop-oozing-americas-white-collar-offices-generative-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkslop%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20neatly%20prepared%20decks%20and%20memos%20that%20are%20often%20lengthy%20but%20lack%20useful%20information.%20%26quot%3BAs%20you%20have%20an%20idea%2C%20you%20should%20also%20have%20your%20strategy%20and%20your%20objectives%2C%20and%20then%20you%20should%20use%20AI%20to%20help%20you%20flush%20out%20the%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Emilie%20DiFranco%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20marketing%20at%20the%20firm%20Marketri.%20DiFranco%20says%20AI%20is%20helpful%20for%20marketers%20because%20it%20can%20review%20and%20consolidate%20data%2C%20but%20relying%20too%20heavily%20on%20AI%20without%20the%20right%20endgame%20for%20a%20marketing%20strategy%20in%20mind%20could%20get%20messy.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20a%20little%20worried%20about%20losing%20the%20human%20aspect%20of%20creating%20that%20initial%20strategy%20and%20the%20objectives%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Marketers%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Bnot%20just%20rolling%20off%20a%20vibe%2C%20but%20making%20sure%20there's%20research%2C%20making%20sure%20you%20have%20those%20foundational%20elements%20before%20you%20engage%20with%20AI%20to%20start%20helping%20you%20put%20the%20plan%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVibing%20is%20in%20vogue%20right%20now.%20As%20companies%20and%20execs%20move%20quickly%20to%20capitalize%20on%20the%20idea%2C%20it%20could%20turn%20cringe.%20But%20work%20is%20still%20work%2C%20and%20trying%20to%20throw%20a%20fun%20twist%20on%20how%20we%20talk%20about%20it%20or%20putting%20generative%20AI%20tools%20in%20the%20mix%20doesn't%20mean%20employers%20aren't%20demanding%20a%20lot%20from%20their%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-vibe-working-coding-microsoft-openai-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1760861221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f276055dbc4fd10dab1026%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busine